🎃 WHEN NOT TO HAVE PAPAYAS 🎃

Papayas have umpteen benefits but EXTRA care is to be given on when you should AVOID eating papaya all together. 
🎃 Papayas in Pregnancy are a big no no. They cause uterine contractions which can lead to abortion. 
🎃 Papaya intake while pregnancy has been linked to birth defects in babies by many researches.
🎃 Papayas should also be avoided by lactating mothers since it can be toxic to babies and cause some serious illnesses. 
🎃 Having papaya more than 1 cup in a day can damage oesophagus. So have papaya in little quantities.
🎃 Papaya is one of those fruits which can cause allergic reaction to people with sensitive immune system. 
🎃 Papaya brings down blood glucose level; if consumed carelessly, blood glucose levels can drop to dangerous levels.
🎃 Papaya Affects male fertility by decreasing sperm count and mobility. 
🎃 Benzyl isothiocyanate is present in it, so consuming it in large quantity can be toxic. 
🎃 It is highly recommended for couples who are trying to conceive or have conceived to avoid papaya intake. 
Enjoy papaya once in a while keeping in mind the above mentioned guidelines.

整體評分：77

很推的一家素食自助餐，我本身不吃素，但當我覺得吃得太油或是需要補充蔬菜的時候就會來這間。其他素食自助餐價位都不比葷食自助餐便宜，但這家是超級便宜，像圖片這樣裝滿滿一盒只要25塊，老闆娘超佛心！！青菜爽脆清甜，少油少鹽，不多做加工，吃得到蔬菜本身的原味；炒麵有點濕軟，不過味道不錯；涼拌青木瓜醃漬得酸酸甜甜、很清爽，大推！！芋丸外皮炸得很酥脆，咬開裡面都是芋泥，這個也很推！！山苦瓜幾乎不會苦。這家健康美味又便宜，推薦給吃素的朋友們！！

🔥Upgraded Avo Toast🔥 

"This cilantro mint chutney is anti-inflammatory, good for your microbiome and makes everything it touches including good ol’ avocado toast utterly irresistible. 

RECIPE: 

🔥Blend 2 cup fresh cilantro (stems are fine too), 1 cup fresh mint leaves, 1 shallot, 1 clove garlic, a 1/2 inch knob of peeled ginger, salt and 1-2 tsp sugar (or to taste) with a splash of water until smooth. You can also add a green chili for heat. 

🔥Slather on toast and top with sliced tomatoes, avocado, salt, sumac, cayenne, hemp hearts and a bit more chutney. 

🔥Also works well as a dip for pakoras, kebabs, or just as a little side kick to your fav meal."

MEET RON FINLEY: also known as the Guerrilla Gardner. He is from South Los Angeles, who noticed that his community had little to no access to healthy and nutritious foods without having to go to another neighborhood. Ron disliked that so he took action by planting a garden right outside his home in 2010. The city gave him a citation because the area he grew fruits and vegetables were owned by the city. Soon after, Ron along with his group LA Green Grounds was able to get the law changed so that no one would be fined for growing food on the sidewalk strips. Believe it or not, he does more than what he is talked about for such as one of his careers as a fashion designer and is an owner of many blaxploitation original posters. As a fashion designer he has created pieces for pro-athletes and most recently did a collab with everybody.world clothing as well as his own merch on his website(right now is sold out). As for his infamous urban gardening, he had his own Masterclass just 8 months ago & presently, still grows plants and they are available for sale through the Ron Finley Project.

三多吉素食/炒麵+白菜+山苦瓜+空心菜/25元
_
整體評分：77
_
很推的一家素食自助餐，我本身不吃素，但當我覺得吃得太油或是需要補充蔬菜的時候就會來這間。其他素食自助餐價位都不比葷食自助餐便宜，但這家是超級便宜，像圖片這樣裝滿滿一盒只要25塊，老闆娘超佛心！！青菜爽脆清甜，少油少鹽，不多做加工，吃得到蔬菜本身的原味；炒麵有點濕軟，不過味道不錯；涼拌青木瓜醃漬得酸酸甜甜、很清爽，大推！！芋丸外皮炸得很酥脆，咬開裡面都是芋泥，這個也很推！！山苦瓜幾乎不會苦。這家健康美味又便宜，推薦給吃素的朋友們！！
_

Wild garlic appearing in the veg patch . I have always grown this garden bully in a pot as left on its own it would soon take over!  I also don’t trust myself to identify it in the wild ! 😂  Its great in a pesto and the delicate white flowers it produces are simply beautiful. Have you ever grown it?

captions:
Pan Kabob - Kabob made in pan!

Simple food for all seasons for busy people! For when you work from home and don’t have much time to spend on cooking! Especially, if you miss or crave kabob!
It was a while since I had cooked this dish and I just thought it would be a good idea and nostalgic of my mom’s cooking. I am so pleased with the taste and it lived up to my expectations! 
Added some pinch of #sumac spice on the rice to complete the flavors and joy! Cook your mom’s best dish and create new memories to live in the hearts of your loved ones! 
I still have work to do for aesthetics! ‎

captions:
A complete plate of happiness: Eggplant dish, rice & tahdig (crispy rice). These days more than ever I am mindful of every little peace of food we consume. On a continuous effort to minimize the amount of food waste in our household. We try to ration our meals as to not waste even a single grain of rice! 
I can only imagine how much hard work from farmers and grocery store staff (just to name a few) have gone into a plate full of food that appears on our table in these difficult times. 
Salut to those who work hard these days so that we have good quality food to eat.

It was time for some Mexican style corn with a bit of a Persian touch and fresh lime! Yum!
